Third-party references
================================================================================

TextMate grammar (syntaxes/quarto.tmLanguage.json)
--------------------------------------------------
This grammar is original work written for this project. It does not embed or
copy any third-party grammar. For prose and plain fenced code blocks it
delegates *by reference* to grammars that ship with Visual Studio Code, by
TextMate scope name only (no source is copied):

  - text.html.markdown   (VS Code built-in Markdown grammar)
  - source.yaml          (YAML, for the front matter)
  - source.python, source.r, source.julia, source.js
                         (embedded code-cell languages; highlighting of r/julia
                          requires the user to have those language grammars
                          installed — they are not bundled with VS Code)

The fenced-block begin/end idiom and the embedded-language injection technique
used here are inspired by the public, MIT-licensed example:

  mjbvz/vscode-fenced-code-block-grammar-injection-example
  https://github.com/mjbvz/vscode-fenced-code-block-grammar-injection-example
  License: MIT

Clean MIT building blocks evaluated while authoring this grammar (not copied):

  - microsoft/vscode-markdown-tm-grammar   (MIT)
  - wooorm/markdown-tm-language            (MIT)

